    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "#4648 actually sets things up so the block import result isn't completed until the payload execute call returns and if the block is optimistically sync'd it isn't considered part of the canonical chain. Then only `AttestationManager` and `BlockManager` are notified of the new block (via `BlockImportNotifications` channel) which is fine as that allows them to process pending attestations and blocks to continue making progress.\n\nAll other notifications are only applied if the block is on the canonical chain which optimistic blocks are not.",
